df.loc: used to access a group of rows and columns by label(s) or a boolean array. loc[] is primarily label based, but may also be used with a boolean array
df.isnull: Detect missing values. Return a boolean same-sized object indicating if the values are NA
df.resample: Resorts the data according to the criteria you give
np.random.randint: Return random integers from the “discrete uniform” distribution of the specified dtype in the “half-open” interval [low, high)
df.cumsum: used to find the cumulative sum value over any axis.
ax.twinx: creates a twin y-axis that shared the x-axis
plt.rcparams: one can dynamically change the default rc settings to customize the default parameters for example through: matplotlib
df.trucate: resizes the file to the given number of bytes